    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Underdark & Caves</em></p>\n<p>A blue-grey herb smelling faintly of nutmeg that heightens the user's senses. Over-dosage or prolonged usage causes photosensitivity, distraction and nervousness; on the other hand, prolonged usage can also make the effects permanent. Nightcall gradually dyes the long-term user's hair, teeth, nails, horns, or scales midnight blue. (The minimum dose of 1 tsp gives the eater +100' sight range, +10% hearing, and +1 to Wisdom and Dexterity scores for up to [[/roll 1d8]] hours. Up to 4 doses will stack, but after the second dose, the user will make a DC 14 Wisdom Save. This DC increases by one after every dosage. If failed, the user becomes addicted and loses -100&rsquo; sight range (down to 3&rsquo;), -10% hearing, and -1 to Wisdom and Dexterity scores while not under Nightcal&rsquo;&rsquo;s effects.)</p>",
